  "prompt": "What are social issues? What some of the types we have?",
  "response": "Social issues are problems or concerns that affect a significant number of people within a society, often related to societal conditions, human rights, and collective well-being. Here are some major types of social issues:\n\n1. Economic Social Issues\n- Poverty\n- Income inequality\n- Unemployment\n- Economic discrimination\n- Minimum wage\n\n2. Racial and Ethnic Issues\n- Racism\n- Discrimination\n- Segregation\n- Racial profiling\n- Cultural marginalization\n\n3. Gender-Related Issues\n- Gender discrimination\n- Sexual harassment\n- Gender pay gap\n- Women's rights\n- LGBTQ+ rights\n\n4. Educational Issues\n- Access to quality education\n- Educational inequality\n- School funding disparities\n- Student debt\n- Digital divide\n\n5. Health-Related Issues\n- Healthcare accessibility\n- Mental health stigma\n- Public health challenges\n- Healthcare affordability\n- Substance abuse\n\n6. Social Justice Issues\n- Human rights\n- Criminal justice reform\n- Social inequality\n- Civil rights\n- Systemic oppression\n\n7. Environmental Issues\n- Climate change\n- Pollution\n- Environmental justice\n- Sustainable development\n- Resource conservation\n\n8. Technology and Social Issues\n- Digital privacy\n- Online harassment\n- Technology addiction\n- Cybersecurity\n- Artificial intelligence ethics\n\nThese categories often intersect and influence each other.",
